b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe07043.htm)  [Next](sbe07045.htm)\n\n* * *\n\np. 140\n\n# XLII.\n\n1\\. Miscellaneous crimes are those which have not been mentioned before.\n\n2\\. Having committed one out of the number of miscellaneous crimes, a prudent\nman should always perform a penance, by the advice of a Brahma _n_ a, after\nthe higher or less degree of his guilt has been ascertained.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: XLIII.](sbe07045.htm)\n\n'